Package: pcie-stub-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends: dkms, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: pcie-access
Description: Generic PCIe BAR access kernel module (DKMS)
 Out-of-tree Linux kernel module that binds to any PCI device,
 maps memory BARs, and exposes a misc character device for MMIO
 reads/writes via ioctl from userspace.
 .
 Features:
  - Binds to any PCI device (vid/device_id params or sysfs new_id)
  - Maps up to 6 memory BARs via pcim_iomap()
  - 8/16/32/64-bit MMIO access with alignment and bounds checking
  - Optional MSI-X, MSI, and legacy INTx interrupt monitoring
  - Safe hot-unplug via kref + rw_semaphore
 .
 This package uses DKMS to automatically build the kernel module
 for your installed kernel(s). Works with stock and custom kernels.

Package: pcie-access
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: pcie-stub-dkms
Description: Userspace CLI tool for PCIe BAR register access
 Command-line utility that communicates with the pcie_access_drv
 kernel module (PCI driver name 'pcie_access') to perform MMIO
 reads/writes on PCI device BARs.
 .
 Usage: pcie_access [DDDD:]BB:DD.F BAR OFFSET TYPE [DATA]
 .
 Supports byte/halfword/dword/qword access widths, full PCI domain
 addressing, and 64-bit offsets. Includes a helper script for
 binding/unbinding PCI devices.
